text.tspan: Buildings
Pipe:
Transfers toxic waste across the map to more
pipes or various buildings.
Input:
Transfers toxic waste from the toxic tank to
your fluid network. You have one from the
beginning, but you can build more (only next
to the Facility).
Output:
Automaticly fills vehicles with fluid. It only fills
a vehicle that is on the same space as this
building. This building needs electricity.
Storage Tank:
This building automaticly collects as much fluid
as possible. It can hold up to 100 units of
toxic waste, but it cannot be emptied! Serves
as a temporary solution for not so temporary
problem.
Radio Tower:
We have no idea who named this building a
"Tower", however it doesn't change the fact
that it calls more cars. Build few of these and
you will have problems filling all those vehicles.
Requires power.
Money Printer:
MONEY!!! This bad boy here gives you precious
money. It needs to be connected to both the
power and fluid grid. Why fluid grid? Because
this building creates even more toxic waste!
Not afraid of a little green water, are we?
Generator:
Generator adds more 10 power units to your
grid. It needs to be connected to the power
grid via the transformer, as any other building
requiring power.
Transformer:
You need this building to connect buildings to
the power grid. It powers all 8 nearest buildings.
Use Transmission Towers to give it power.
Transmission Tower:
This pile of steel delivers power from power
plant to both other Transmission Towers and
Transformers. It can connect buildings in the
range of up to 5 tiles.
